UkYorkshirelass99
UK144 contributions
Just great!
Jul 2023
My sister got Mens Final tickets in the ballot after years of trying. We used the shuttle bus from Wimbledon Station and arrived at the gates by 9am. Very small queue which grew very quickly. Entry on the dot of 10 was well organised and speedy. We headed straight to the fabulous museum, full of well displayed, interesting items. Next stop Herman Hill where we enjoyed a Pimms in the sunshine and bought lunch. Efficient service and good quality, well priced food and drinks. Centre Court looked splendid and the Men’s Final was fabulous. We returned to Centre Court to catch some of the Ladies Doubles final. Felt so sorry for the players that there were so few spectators. Could this match not be played before the Men’s Final to attract a bigger audience and improved atmosphere on court for the players? All the staff we met were polite and helpful, especially the service lady on duty on Block 110. Caught the shuttle bus back to Wimbledon Station just after 9pm. Wonderful day from start to finish!
Written July 18, 2023

Brillliant day, great atmosphere, totally unique experience
Jul 2023 • Couples
Been trying the ballot for years and finally got tickets this year for July 9th, the day did not disappoint , we had tickets for court number 1 which didn’t start till 1pm we went for about 10.30am to spend some time in the grounds which I would recommend we even spent a bit of time on one of the outside courts 18 just to experience a court close up , as it was early we didn’t have to queue we just walked on , at 1pm we were sat in number 1 court , the good thing about Wimbledon is the day can be as inexpensive as you want it to be you can take your own food and drink , we took some cocktail cans but did have a pimms as well but drink can be quite costly at 10pd per pimms , food again can be as cheap as you want we opted for the 12 picnic express 4 items for 12 pds and this can include the 2.50 strawberries and cream which were great 10 strawberries included.

We got to see 3 great matches the last being the best we were on the second last row and still had a great view and the atmosphere is amazing , would recommend anyone visit if their lucky to get tickets it’s a unique experience.

Still the old Court One!
Jul 2023 • Couples
The same old Court One - sad and lonely place to watch tennis on Week One. In spite of the upgrades, the new roof and seating, the scheduling and placement of matches does not represent the now-close to Centre Court priced tickets. Three British players in matches on Thursday, and not one on Court 1. The court was at least a third empty most of the time, and often half-full as the spectators witnessed three dull matches with no local interest - consequently the Andy Murray match late on Centre Court did not complete by 11pm, and he ultimately lost on Friday! We realise the corporate business is important to Wimbledon, but the lack of attention to the real fans of tennis who every year support the tournament is particularly evident this year.
Written July 8, 2023

Helen S

The Queue
Jul 2023 • Friends
My friends and I had a really bad experience with the Wimbledon “queue” today. It’s been many years since we went to Wimbledon and had read the newspaper reports about searching all bags and random body searches, so we knew the wait would take a while. We asked the steward when we arrived at the queue at 08:00 whether we had any chance of getting into the grounds on the day and were told “yes”.

Our queue ticket number was 11772+. We sat like all those around us on the grass, not moving until 11:30ish when it was our queue’s turn to move forward. Not sure what happened (perhaps not enough stewards in the vicinity) but every queue to our left and numbers up to 14000+ started moving at the same time, it was absolute chaos and although we moved to another part of the field the orderly queue in sequential numbers was by now in mayhem with hundreds of guests mixed up. We stayed where we had ended up but by 13:00 it was obviously going to be difficult to ensure everyone would get into the grounds in the correct order which was totally unfair on everyone and, like us, many people gave up. There was no delimiting between the lines of people and far too few stewards in our opinion. Utterly disappointed and a waste of time, early start and train ticket money.
Written July 7, 2023
